abstract: A United Nations report says Afghanistan passed a grim milestone with more than 100,000 civilians killed or hurt in the last 10 years since the international body began documenting casualties in a war that has raged for 18 years.
snippet: A United Nations report says Afghanistan passed a grim milestone with more than 100,000 civilians killed or hurt in the last 10 years since the international body began documenting casualties in a war that has raged for 18 years.
lead_paragraph: KABUL, Afghanistan — A United Nations report says Afghanistan passed a grim milestone with more than 100,000 civilians killed or hurt in the last 10 years since the international body began documenting casualties in a war that has raged for 18 years.
headline_main: UN: 100,000 Civilians Casualties in Afghanistan in 10 Years
headline_print_headline: UN: 100,000 Civilians Casualties in Afghanistan in 10 Years

abstract: U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's campaign has pumped $25.7 million into his little-known tech company Hawkfish since the billionaire entered the race last November, according to disclosures to the Federal Election Commission.
snippet: U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's campaign has pumped $25.7 million into his little-known tech company Hawkfish since the billionaire entered the race last November, according to disclosures to the Federal Election Commiss...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's campaign has pumped $25.7 million into his little-known tech company Hawkfish since the billionaire entered the race last November, according to disclosures to the Federal Election Commission.
headline_main: Bloomberg Campaign Builds Out Digital Arm Hawkfish Ahead of 2020 Election
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Campaign Builds Out Digital Arm Hawkfish Ahead of 2020 Election

abstract: The vote was 5 to 4, with the Supreme Court’s conservatives in the majority.
snippet: The vote was 5 to 4, with the Supreme Court’s conservatives in the majority.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court on Friday allowed the Trump administration to move forward with plans to deny green cards to immigrants who are thought to be likely to become “public charges” by making even occasional and minor use of public benefits like Medicaid, food stamps and housing vouchers.

abstract: Privatization has ushered in mold, mismanagement and worse.
snippet: Privatization has ushered in mold, mismanagement and worse.
lead_paragraph: Living on a military base can be idyllic. Children bike and run freely, cars drive slowly through the neighborhoods, parents keep an eye on one another’s kids, uniformed service members pop home for lunch, and everybody knows your name. In recent years however, these Mayberrys have been plagued by substantial unresolved maintenance issues, which many military renters chalk up to abject negligence from private military housing companies.

abstract: A federal judge on Friday dismissed a racketeering lawsuit brought by Republican Rep. Devin Nunes against the political research firm that enlisted a former British spy to look into Donald Trump’s ties to Russia during the 2016 presidential campaign.
snippet: A federal judge on Friday dismissed a racketeering lawsuit brought by Republican Rep. Devin Nunes against the political research firm that enlisted a former British spy to look into Donald Trump’s ties to Russia during the 2016 presidential campai...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal judge on Friday dismissed a racketeering lawsuit brought by Republican Rep. Devin Nunes against the political research firm that enlisted a former British spy to look into Donald Trump’s ties to Russia during the 2016 presidential campaign.
headline_main: Judge Dismisses Nunes Lawsuit Against Fusion GPS
headline_print_headline: Judge Dismisses Nunes Lawsuit Against Fusion GPS

abstract: What happens when intelligence officials warn that Russia is meddling in American politics again? Donald Trump gets mad — at the intelligence officials.
snippet: What happens when intelligence officials warn that Russia is meddling in American politics again? Donald Trump gets mad — at the intelligence officials.
lead_paragraph: President Trump is intensifying his efforts to undermine the nation’s intelligence agencies.

abstract: The party’s riskiest bet is now its likeliest.
snippet: The party’s riskiest bet is now its likeliest.
lead_paragraph: I’ve been enthusiastic about Mike Bloomberg’s race for president from its inception, partly on the theory that he was best positioned to rescue and represent the Democratic Party’s moderate wing. After Wednesday night’s debate debacle in Las Vegas, I’m starting to fear his candidacy might inadvertently destroy that wing — while wrecking the party’s chances in November.

abstract: The administration’s plan to divert more military funds to building a border wall is the latest example of the long-running erosion of Congress’s power of the purse.
snippet: The administration’s plan to divert more military funds to building a border wall is the latest example of the long-running erosion of Congress’s power of the purse.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When the Pentagon announced this month that it would divert billions more dollars in military funding to the construction of President Trump’s border wall, bipartisan outrage ricocheted across Capitol Hill.

abstract: Under Prime Minister Narendra Modi, India is the American president’s spiritual home: an inferno of systemic cruelty.
snippet: Under Prime Minister Narendra Modi, India is the American president’s spiritual home: an inferno of systemic cruelty.
lead_paragraph: “I love Hindu,” Donald Trump proclaimed during his presidential campaign in 2016. That adoration of India’s majority population, and America’s richest and most obviously pro-Trump minority, may have just gotten deeper.
